mentor.name: Tohu Wa-Bohu

choice.name: Magician: Gain the Witness My Hate quality for free.

choice.name: Adept: Gain the Adept Accident power for free.

mentor.altdisadvantage: Followers gain the Driven quality, in which the focus is the opportunity to destroy something meaningful. Further, they fnd it hard to work in groups given their destructive nature. They can never beneft from teamwork or leadership bonuses.

mentor.name: Green Man

choice.name: Magician: +2 dice pool modifer to summon Plant Spirits.
choice.translate: Magician: +2 dice pool modifer to summon Plant Spirits.

choice.name: Adept: Gain 2 free levels of Rooting.

mentor.altadvantage: All: +2 dice pool modifer for Negotiation Tests.
mentor.altdisadvantage: When signifcant damage is being done to vegetation, they must pass a Charisma + Willpower (3) Test or use all means possible to stop the destruction.

mentor.name: Sun

choice.name: Magician: +2 dice pool modifer when casting Sun- or Fire-based spells.
choice.translate: Magician: +2 dice pool modifer when casting Sun- or Fire-based spells.

choice.name: Adept: Gain 3 free levels of Temperature Tolerance
choice.translate: Adept: Gain 3 free levels of Temperature Tolerance

mentor.altadvantage: All: +2 dice pool modifer for Perception tests when outside during the day.
mentor.altdisadvantage: Followers of Sun must pass a Charisma + Willpower (4) Test in order to purposefully deceive others.

mentor.name: Dark King

choice.name: Magician: +2 dice to Contractual Rituals.
choice.translate: Magician: +2 dice to Contractual Rituals.

choice.name: Adept: Gain Spirit Ram for free.
choice.translate: Adept: Gain Spirit Ram for free.

mentor.altadvantage: All: +2 dice to Intimidation tests.
mentor.altdisadvantage: Followers receive a –1 dice pool penalty when resisting physical damage.

mentor.name: Moon

choice.name: Magician: +2 dice for Illusion and transformation-focused Manipulation spells, preparations, and spell rituals.
choice.translate: Magician: +2 dice for Illusion and transformation-focused Manipulation spells, preparations, and spell rituals.

choice.name: Adept: Gain 3 levels of Stillness for free.
choice.translate: Adept: Gain 3 levels of Stillness for free.

mentor.altadvantage: All: +2 dice to Negotiation tests.
mentor.altdisadvantage: Followers of Moon must make a Charisma + Willpower (4) Test in order to engage in direct confrontation; failure means they cannot make any action considered as such. Negotiation is not considered confrontation (Moon loves discussion), but arguments fall into that category.

mentor.name: Oak

choice.name: Magician: +2 dice pool bonus when summoning plant or air spirits (choose 1 when selecting this mentor spirit).
choice.translate: Magician: +2 dice pool bonus when summoning plant or air spirits (choose 1 when selecting this mentor spirit).

choice.name: Adept: Gain 2 levels of Stillness for free

mentor.altadvantage: All: +1 to Damage Resistance tests.
mentor.altdisadvantage: Must have a natural (meaning unaugmented) Body and Strength of 4 or greater to select this mentor spirit.

choice.name: Magician: +2 to summoning earth spirits.
choice.translate: Magician: +2 to summoning earth spirits.

choice.name: Adept: Gain +2 levels of Light Body for free.
choice.translate: Adept: Gain +2 levels of Light Body for free.

mentor.altadvantage: All: +2 to Blades tests.
mentor.altdisadvantage: Followers of the Stag demand respect, especially to those they give it to. Once disrespected, they must succeed in a Charisma + Willpower (3) Test, or they will demand satisfaction against the slight.

mentor.name: Spider (Alt)

choice.name: Magician: +2 dice pool modifer when casting Manipulation spells, preparations, and rituals
choice.translate: Magician: +2 dice pool modifer when casting Manipulation spells, preparations, and rituals

choice.name: Adept: Gain 2 free levels of Spirit Claw (although in this case, it manifests as a fang).
choice.translate: Adept: Gain 2 free levels of Spirit Claw (although in this case, it manifests as a fang).

mentor.altadvantage: All: +2 dice pool modifer for tests using the Stealth skill group.
mentor.altdisadvantage: When not following a plan or a plan doesn’t go according to plan, followers of Spider must pass a Charisma + Willpower (4) Test or suffer –2 to all rolls until a new plan is established.

mentor.name: Wolf (Alt)

choice.name: Magician: +1 dice pool modifer when casting Combat spells, preparations, and rituals.
choice.translate: Magician: +1 dice pool modifer when casting Combat spells, preparations, and rituals.

choice.name: Adept: Gain 2 free levels of Danger Sense.
choice.translate: Adept: Gain 2 free levels of Danger Sense.

mentor.altdisadvantage: Whenever a follower of Wolf sees an opportunity to survive by attacking or sacrifcing the weak, they must pass a Charisma + Willpower (4) Test or attempt to seize the opportunity. This does not apply to those the Wolf considers friends or family.

mentor.name: Rat (Alt)

choice.name: Magician: +1 dice pool modifer when casting Health spells, preparations, and rituals
choice.translate: Magician: +1 dice pool modifer when casting Health spells, preparations, and rituals

choice.name: Adept: Gain 1 free level of Analytics.
choice.translate: Adept: Gain 1 free level of Analytics.

mentor.altadvantage: All: +1 dice pool modifer for tests using the Perception and Sneaking skills.
mentor.altdisadvantage: Followers of Rat cannot receive aid or aid others with a Teamwork test unless they trust the individuals they are teaming with. Further, if they do trust the individuals, but that trust is broken through incompetence or betrayal, they must pass a Charisma + Willpower (4) Test to be able to use teamwork with that individual each time in the future.

mentor.advantage: +1 Würfel für das Kompilieren und Registrieren von Sprites jeder Art.
mentor.disadvantage: Null-Eins ist die Perfektion des Codes und verlangt seinen Anhängern das Gleiche ab oder erteilt ihnen zumindest eine harte Lektion, wenn sie fehlschlagen. Null-Eins-Technomancer müssen 2 Punkte Edge ausgeben, um einen Patzer zu negieren oder einen kritischen Patzer abzuschwächen.

mentor.name: Alias
mentor.advantage: +2 Würfel auf Verschleierungsproben, +1 Würfel für Infiltrator- oder Spürhund-Sprites (Spieler muss sich für einen der beiden entscheiden)
mentor.disadvantage: Alias-Technomancer können es nicht ertragen, für ihren Lebensunterhalt zu zahlen, und müssen daher ihre Fähigkeiten einsetzen, um einen Lebensstil vorzutäuschen (siehe Handbuch für Hacker, S. 86).

mentor.name: Abort
mentor.advantage: +2 Würfel auf alle Absturzproben, +1 Würfel für dissonante Infiltrator- oder Stör-Sprites (eine Sorte wählen)
mentor.disadvantage: Einem Abbruch-Technomancer muss eine Willenskraft + Charisma (3)-Probe gelingen, um im Matrixkampf eine andere Handlung auszuführen als die Software seiner Gegner zum Absturz zu bringen.

mentor.name: Archivist
mentor.advantage: +2 Würfel auf alle Schmökerproben, +1 Würfel für Code- oder Daten-Sprites (Spieler muss sich für einen der beiden entscheiden)
mentor.disadvantage: Technomancer, die dem Archivar folgen, können nicht absichtlich Daten vernichten oder beschädigen. Dem Technomancer muss eine Willenskraft + Logik (3)-Probe gelingen, um absichtlich Daten zu löschen oder zu beschädigen (oder um einen Sprite dazu zu instruieren).

mentor.name: Architect
mentor.advantage: +2 Würfel auf Editier-Proben, +1 Würfel für Daten- oder Maschinen-Sprites (Spieler muss sich für einen der beiden entscheiden)
mentor.disadvantage: –1 Würfel auf Absturz-Proben

mentor.name: Babel
mentor.advantage: +1 auf online abgelegte Gebräuche- und Sprachproben, +1 Würfel für Kurier- oder Lehrer-Sprites (Spieler muss sich für einen der beiden entscheiden)
mentor.disadvantage: Geheimhaltung ist ein Fluch für die Kommunikation, daher muss Babel-Technomancern eine Willenskraft + Logik (3)-Probe gelingen, um etwas zu verschlüsseln.

mentor.name: The Black Hat
mentor.advantage: +2 Würfel auf Ausnutzen-Proben, +1 Würfel für Infiltrator- oder Stör-Sprites (Spieler muss sich für einen der beiden entscheiden)
mentor.disadvantage: Technomancer, die dem Schwarzen Hut folgen, können nur schwer der Versuchung widerstehen, in einen Knoten einzudringen, der ihnen irgendwie interessant erscheint. Dem Technomancer muss eine Willenskraft + Charisma (3)-Probe gelingen, um dieser Versuchung zu widerstehen, wenn sich eine entsprechende Gelegenheit ergibt.

mentor.name: Cryptome
mentor.advantage: +2 Würfel auf alle Verschlüsselungs- und Entschlüsselungs-Proben, +1 Würfel für Daten- oder Kurier-Sprites (Spieler muss sich für einen der beiden entscheiden)
mentor.disadvantage: Technomancer, die Kryptom folgen, geben Geheimnisse nur ungern aus der Hand, und schon gar nicht an unzuverlässige Quellen. Dem Technomancer muss eine Willenskraft + Logik (3)-Probe gelingen, um ein Geheimnis oder eine vertrauliche Information an jemanden weiterzugeben, dem er nicht vollständig vertraut – und solches Vertrauen ist selten.

mentor.name: Daedalus
mentor.advantage: +2 Würfel auf Hardware-Proben, +1 Würfel für Maschinen- oder Stör-Sprites (Spieler muss sich für einen der beiden entscheiden)
mentor.disadvantage: Technomancer, die Daedalus folgen, interagieren mit Maschinen, an oder mit denen sie arbeiten, noch unterbewusster als üblich. Daher sind Modifikationen, die sie einbauen, eher auf Leute mit ihren Gaben und ihrer Weltsicht ausgerichtet und weniger etwas, was für Weltliche oder auch Nicht-Daedalus-Technomancer intuitiv einsichtig wäre. Geräte, die von solchen Technomancern gebaut oder modifiziert werden, haben ein undurchsichtigeres Interface als normal und bringen jedem, der sie benutzen will, einen Modifikator von –2.

mentor.name: Delphi
mentor.advantage: +2 Würfel auf Analyse-Proben, +1 Würfel für Code- oder Lehrer-Sprites (Spieler muss sich für einen der beiden entscheiden)
mentor.disadvantage: Delphi-Technomancer können sich nicht gut auf unerwartete Situationen einstellen. Ihnen muss eine Willenskraft + Logik (3)-Probe gelingen, um in Situationen, die sie nicht eingeplant haben, eine schnelle Entscheidung zu treffen.

mentor.name: Disinformation
mentor.advantage: +1 Würfel auf alle Proben auf Fertigkeiten aus der Einfluss-Fertigkeitsgruppe, +1 Würfel für dissonante Daten- oder Lehrer-Sprites (eine Sorte wählen)
mentor.disadvantage: Desinformations-Technomancern muss eine Willenskraft + Charisma (3)-Probe gelingen, um wahre, vollständige oder nicht-manipulierte Informationen über die Matrix an nicht-dissonante Technomancer weiterzugeben.

mentor.name: Echelon
mentor.advantage: +1 Würfel auf Aufspüren- und Schnüffler-Proben, +1 Würfel für Infiltrator- oder Spürhund-Sprites (Spieler muss sich für einen der beiden entscheiden)
mentor.disadvantage: Anhänger von Lauscher arbeiten besessen daran, Informationen über alles zu sammeln, was um sie herum vorgeht. Wenn sie unvorbereitet, ohne die von ihnen benötigten Informationen, erwischt werden oder sie blind in eine Situation geraten, erleiden sie einen Würfelpoolmodifikator von –1 auf alle Handlungen, solange diese Situation anhält.

mentor.name: Flow
mentor.advantage: +2 Würfel auf Improvisations-Proben, +1 Würfel für Code- oder Daten-Sprites (Spieler muss sich für einen der beiden entscheiden)
mentor.disadvantage: –1 Würfel auf Angriffsproben beim Matrixkampf.

mentor.name: Idoru
mentor.advantage: +2 Würfel auf Überreden-Proben, +1 Würfel für Infiltrator- oder Spürhund-Sprites (Spieler muss sich für einen der beiden entscheiden)
mentor.disadvantage: Anhängern von Idoru muss eine Willenskraft + Logik (3)-Probe gelingen, um Daten nicht zu ihren Gunsten zu manipulieren, wenn es die Situation erfordert.

mentor.name: Intrusion Countermeasure (IC)
mentor.advantage: +2 Würfel auf alle Matrix-Schadenswiderstandproben außer Schwund, +1 Würfel für Paladin-Sprites
mentor.disadvantage: Wenn es einem IC-Technomancer misslingt, etwas zu schützen, für das er sich verantwortlich fühlt, oder wenn er ein selbst gestecktes Ziel nicht erreicht, erleidet er einen Würfelpoolmodifikator von –1 auf alle Handlungen, bis er für sein Versagen Buße getan hat.

mentor.name: Jormungand
mentor.advantage: +2 Würfel auf Korrumpieren-Proben, +1 Würfel für dissonante Code- oder Daten-Sprites (eine Sorte wählen)
mentor.disadvantage: Jormungand-Technomancer sind destruktiv und werden jede Gelegenheit nutzen, einen Knoten zu verwüsten, indem sie seine Daten permanent vernichten oder korrumpieren. Ihnen muss eine Willenskraft + Logik (3)-Probe gelingen, um einen Knoten, in den sie gehackt sind, unbeschädigt zu lassen.

mentor.name: Nemesis
mentor.advantage: +2 Würfel auf Überreden-Proben, +1 Würfel für dissonante Spürhund- oder Stör-Sprites (eine Sorte wählen)
mentor.disadvantage: Einem Nemesis-Technomancer muss eine Willenskraft + Charisma (3)-Probe gelingen, um sich selbst davon abzuhalten, jene zu bestrafen, die es seiner Meinung nach verdient haben.

mentor.name: Noise
mentor.advantage: +2 Würfel auf Improvisierenproben, +1 Würfel für dissonante Code- oder Kurier-Sprites (eine Sorte wählen)
mentor.disadvantage: Rauschen-Technomancer sind mehr als andere vom ständigen Flüstern der Matrix abhängig, daher erleiden sie die doppelten Modifikatoren auf Matrix- und Nicht-Matrix-Handlungen, wenn sie sich in statischen oder toten Zonen befinden

mentor.name: Probe
mentor.advantage: +2 Würfel auf alle Scan-Proben, +1 Würfel für Infiltrator- oder Spürhund-Sprites (Spieler muss sich für einen der beiden entscheiden)
mentor.disadvantage: Sonden-Technomancer erhalten einen Würfelpoolmodifikator von –2 auf Eiliges Hacken, also wenn sie nicht vorher das Ziel sondieren.

mentor.name: Pulse
mentor.advantage: +2 Würfel auf Matrixinitiative-Proben
mentor.disadvantage: –2 Würfel auf Hacking-Proben, wenn nicht eilig gehackt wird.

mentor.name: Shooter
mentor.advantage: +2 Würfel auf alle Matrix-Angriffsproben, +1 Würfel für Paladin- oder Panzer-Sprites (Spieler muss sich für einen der beiden entscheiden).
mentor.disadvantage: Einem Technomancer, der Todesschütze folgt, muss eine Willenskraft + Logik (3)-Probe gelingen, um sich aus einem Matrixkampf zurückzuziehen.

mentor.name: Snuff
mentor.advantage: +2 Würfel auf alle Schnüffler-Proben, +1 Würfel für dissonante Infiltrator- oder Spürhund-Sprites (eine Sorte wählen)
mentor.disadvantage: Snuff-Technomancer erleiden einen Würfelpoolmodifikator von –2 bei Widerstandsproben gegen die Abhängigkeit von BTL oder Matrixmedien.

mentor.name: Tiamat
mentor.advantage: +2 Würfel auf Matrixkampf, +2 Würfel für dissonante Infiltrator- oder Panzer-Sprites (eine Sorte wählen)
mentor.disadvantage: –1 Würfel auf alle Hackingproben

mentor.name: The World Tree
mentor.advantage: +2 Würfel auf Analyse-Proben, +1 Würfel für Code- oder Kurier-Sprites (Spieler muss sich für einen der beiden entscheiden)
mentor.disadvantage: Weltenbaum-Technomancer lassen sich leicht von Informationen ablenken, die sie interessant finden. Wenn er sich neuen Informationen, ungewöhnlichen Daten oder Phänomenen gegenübersieht, muss dem Technomancer eine Willenskraft + Charisma (3)-Probe gelingen, um der Versuchung zu widerstehen, seine momentane Aufgabe liegen zu lassen und die Informationen zu analysieren und an sich zu bringen (falls möglich).

improvement.name: Attribute
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the values for one of the character's Attributes. Positive numbers increase an Attribute. Negative numbers decrease an Attribute. Select an Attribute to affect by clicking the Select Value button. Value adjusts the Attribute's current value. Minimum adjusts the Metatype's minimum value for the Attribute. Maximum adjusts the Metatype's maximum value for the Attribute. Metatype augmented maximum values are automatically adjusted based on the new Metatype maximum. Fields may be left at 0 if you do not want to affect that particular aspect of the Attribute.

improvement.name: Condition Monitor, Physical
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the number of boxes the character has in their Physical Condition Monitor. Positive numbers increase the number of boxes in the Condition Monitor. Negative numbers reduce the number of boxes in the Condition Monitor.

improvement.name: Condition Monitor, Stun
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the number of boxes the character has in their Stun Condition Monitor. Positive numbers increase the number of boxes in the Condition Monitor. Negative numbers reduce the number of boxes in the Condition Monitor.

improvement.name: Condition Monitor, Threshold
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the number of boxes between each Condition Monitor Threshold. Positive numbers increase the number of boxes between each Threshold. Negative numbers reduce the number of boxes between each Threshold.

improvement.name: Condition Monitor, Threshold Offset
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the number of boxes between the start of each Condition Monitor and the first Threshold. Positive numbers increase the starting position of the first Threshold. Negative numbers reduce the starting position of each Threshold.

improvement.name: Living Persona, Device Rating
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the Living Persona's Device Rating by the value entered. Positive numbers improve the Device Rating. Negative numbers reduce the Device Rating. You may enter XPath operations as well. This has no effect on characters that do not have a Living Persona.

improvement.name: Living Persona, Program Limit
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the Living Persona's Program Limit by the value entered. Positive numbers improve the Program Limit. Negative numbers reduce the Program Limit. You may enter XPath operations as well. This has no effect on characters that do not have a Living Persona.

improvement.name: Living Persona, Attack
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the Living Persona's Attack by the value entered. Positive numbers improve Attack. Negative numbers reduce Attack. You may enter XPath operations as well. This has no effect on characters that do not have a Living Persona.

improvement.name: Living Persona, Sleaze
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the Living Persona's Sleaze by the value entered. Positive numbers improve Sleaze. Negative numbers reduce Sleaze. You may enter XPath operations as well. This has no effect on characters that do not have a Living Persona.

improvement.name: Living Persona, Data Processing
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the Living Persona's Data Processing by the value entered. Positive numbers improve Data Processing. Negative numbers reduce Data Processing. You may enter XPath operations as well. This has no effect on characters that do not have a Living Persona.

improvement.name: Living Persona, Firewall
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the Living Persona's Firewall by the value entered. Positive numbers improve Firewall. Negative numbers reduce Firewall. You may enter XPath operations as well. This has no effect on characters that do not have a Living Persona.

improvement.name: Skill
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the value for one of the character's Skills by the value entered. Positive numbers increase the Skill. Negative numbers decrease the Skill. Select a Skill to affect by clicking the Select Value button. The modifier can be applied to the Skill's Rating by selecting Apply to Rating, otherwise the modifier is applied as a dice pool modifier.

improvement.name: Skills in Category
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the value for all of the Skills in one category by the value entered. Positive numbers increase the Skills. Negative numbers decrease the Skills. Select a Skill category to affect by clicking the Select Value button. The modifier can be applied to the Skills' Ratings by selecting Apply to Rating, otherwise the modifier is applied as a dice pool modifier.

improvement.name: Skills in Group
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the value for all of the Skills in a Skill Group by the value entered. Positive numbers increase the Skills. Negative numbers decrease the Skills. Select a Skill Group to affect by clicking the Select Value button. The modifier can be applied to the Skills' Ratings by selecting Apply to Rating, otherwise the modifier is applied as a dice pool modifier.

improvement.name: Skills linked to Attribute
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the value for all of the Skills linked to an Attribute by the value entered. Positive numbers increase the Skills. Negative numbers decrease the Skills. Select a linked Attribute to affect by clicking the Select Value button. The modifier can be applied to the Skills' Ratings by selecting Apply to Rating, otherwise the modifier is applied as a dice pool modifier.

improvement.name: Armor, Ballistic
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the character's Ballistic Armor Rating by the value entered. Positive numbers improve Ballistic Armor. Negative numbers reduce Ballistic Armor.

improvement.name: Armor, Impact
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the character's Impact Armor Rating by the value entered. Positive numbers improve Impact Armor. Negative numbers reduce Impact Armor.

improvement.name: Reach
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the character's Reach by the value entered. Positive numbers increase Reach. Negative numbers reduce Reach.

improvement.name: Unarmed DV
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the Damage Value for a character's Unarmed Attacks by the value entered. Positive numbers increase the Damage Value. Negative numbers decrease the Damage Value.

improvement.name: Unarmed DV Physical
improvement.altpage: All of the character's Unarmed Attacks will do Physical damage instead of Stun damage.

improvement.name: Unarmed AP
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the Armor Penetration value for a character's Unarmed Attacks by the value entered. Positive numbers reduce Armor Penetration. Negative numbers increase Armor Penetration.

improvement.name: Initiative
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the character's Initiative by the value entered. Positive numbers increase Initiative. Negative numbers reduce Initiative.

improvement.name: Matrix Initiative
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the character's Matrix Initiative by the value entered. Positive numbers increase Matrix Initiative. Negative numbers reduce Matrix Initiative.

improvement.name: Lifestyle Cost
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the Nuyen cost of all Lifestyles by the percent value entered. All Lifestyles will now cost an additional X% per month. Positive number increase the Lifestyle's monthly Nuyen cost. Negative numbers reduce the Lifestyle's monthly Nuyen cost.

improvement.name: Genetech Cost
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the Nuyen cost of Bioware in the Genetech categories by the percent value entered. All Genetech Nuyen costs will now be X% of their original value. Numbers lower than 100 reduce the Nuyen cost. Numbers higher than 100 increase the Nuyen cost.

improvement.name: Basic Bioware Essence Cost
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the Essence cost of Bioware in the Basic category by the percent value entered. All Basic Bioware Essence costs will now be X% of their original value. Numbers lower than 100 reduce the Essence cost. Numbers higher than 100 increase the Essence cost.

improvement.name: Bioware Essence Cost
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the Essence cost of Bioware by the percent value entered. All Bioware Essence costs will now be X% of their original value. Numbers lower than 100 reduce the Essence cost. Numbers higher than 100 increase the Essence cost.

improvement.name: Cyberware Essence Cost
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the Essence cost of Cyberware by the percent value entered. All Cyberware Essence costs will now be X% of their original value. Numbers lower than 100 reduce the Essence cost. Numbers higher than 100 increase the Essence cost.

improvement.name: Weapon Category DV
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the Damage Value of all Weapons in the selected category by the value entered. Positive numbers increase Weapon Damage Value. Negative numbers decrease Weapon Damage Value.

improvement.name: Power Points, Free Spirit
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the number of Power Points a Free Spirit receives to spend on Critter Powers by the value entered. Positive numbers increase the number of Power Points. Negative numbers decrease the number of Power Points. This has no effect on non-Free Spirit characters.

improvement.name: Power Points, Adept
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the number of Power Points an Adept receives to spend on Adept Powers by the value entered. Positive numbers increase the number of Power Points. Negative numbers decrease the number of Power Points. This has no effect on non-Adept characters.

improvement.name: Armor Encumbrance Penalty
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the character's Armor Encumbrance penalty by the value entered. Positive numbers increase the Armor Encumbrance penalty (bad). Negative numbers decrease the Armor Encumbrance penalty (good).

improvement.name: Damage Resistance
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the size of the character's Damage Resistance Test dice pool by the value entered. Positive numbers increase the size of the pool. Negative numbers decrease the size of the pool.

improvement.name: Judge Intentions
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the character's Judge Intentions Special Attribute by the value entered. Positive numbers improve Judge Intentions. Negative numbers reduce Judge Intentions.

improvement.name: Composure
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the character's Composure Special Attribute by the value entered. Positive numbers improve Composure. Negative numbers reduce Composure.

improvement.name: Lift and Carry
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the character's Lift and Carry Special Attribute by the value entered. Positive numbers improve Lift and Carry. Negative numbers reduce Lift and Carry.

improvement.name: Memory
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the character's Memory Special Attribute by the value entered. Positive numbers improve Memory. Negative numbers reduce Memory.

improvement.name: Concealability
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the character's ability to conceal Weapons by the value entered. This bonus applies to the Concealability of all Weapons. Positive values improve Concealability. Negative values reduce Concealability.

improvement.name: Drain Resistance
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the size of the character's Drain Resistance pool by the value entered. Positive values increase the size of the pool. Negative values decrease the size of the pool.

improvement.name: Fading Resistance
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the size of the character's Fading Resistance pool by the value entered. Positive values increase the size of the pool. Negative values decrease the size of the pool.

improvement.name: Spells in Category
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the size of the character's Spellcasting pool when casting Spell in the selected category. Positive values improve Spellcasting. Negative values reduce Spellcasting.

improvement.name: Skillsoft Access
improvement.altpage: The character can use Knowsoft and Linguasoft Skillsofts as though they had a direct neural link.

improvement.name: Essence Maximum
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the character's Maximum Essence by the value entered. Positive values increase Maximum Essence. Negative values decrease Maximum Essence.

improvement.name: Throwing Weapon Range
improvement.altpage: Adjusts a character's STR for the purpose of determining the range of Throwing Weapons. Positive numbers increase the character's effective STR. Negative numbers reduce the character's effective STR.

improvement.name: Skillwire Rating
improvement.altpage: Grants the character access to Skillwires at the specified Rating which limits the effective Rating of all Skillsofts the character takes.

improvement.name: Swap Skill Attribute (Physical for Mental)
improvement.altpage: Swaps the Physical Attribute used by Active Skills with the corresponding Mental Attribute as described in the Astral Attributes table on SR4 192. (AGI/LOG; BOD/WIL; REA/INT; STR/CHA)

improvement.name: Quickening
improvement.altpage: Grants the character access to Quickening in the same manner as the Quickening Metamagic.

improvement.name: Basic Lifestyle Cost
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the Nuyen cost of all basic Lifestyles by the percent value entered. All basic Lifestyles will now cost an additional X% per month. Basic Lifestyles are only those found in the SR4 book and do not include Advanced Lifestyles, Safehouses, or Bolt Holes. Positive number increase the basic Lifestyle's monthly Nuyen cost. Negative numbers reduce the basic Lifestyle's monthly Nuyen cost.

improvement.name: Throwing Weapon STR
improvement.altpage: Adjusts a character's STR for the purpose of determining the DV of Throwing Weapons. Positive numbers increase the character's effective STR. Negative numbers reduce the character's effective STR.

improvement.name: Knowledge Skill
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the value for one of the character's Knowledge Skills by the value entered. Positive numbers increase the Knowledge Skill. Negative numbers decrease the Knowledge Skill. Select a Knowledge Skill to affect by clicking the Select Value button. The modifier can be applied to the Knowledge Skill's Rating by selecting Apply to Rating, otherwise the modifier is applied as a dice pool modifier.

improvement.name: Ignore Condition Monitor Penalty, Stun
improvement.altpage: Reduces the characters Stun Condition Monitor Penalty to 0 while the Improvement is active.

improvement.name: Ignore Condition Monitor Penalty, Physical
improvement.altpage: Reduces the characters Physical Condition Monitor Penalty to 0 while the Improvement is active.

improvement.name: Enable Special Attribute
improvement.altpage: Unlocks the controls for an attribute, allowing the values to be increased. Expected values are MAG, RES or DEP for Magic, Resonance and Depth respectively.

improvement.name: Replace Attribute
improvement.altpage: Overrides the Metatype limitations for an attribute. Minimum adjusts the Metatype's minimum value for the Attribute. Maximum adjusts the Metatype's maximum value for the Attribute. Metatype augmented maximum values are automatically adjusted based on the new Metatype maximum.

improvement.name: Enable Spells and Spirits Tab
improvement.altpage: Enables the character's Spells and Spirits tab, allowing them to buy spells and bind spirits. The character is flagged as a Magician for the purposes of quality requirements, but does not receive access to the Initiation tab, unlock their Magic attribute or receive any of the Magical skills. Incompatible with improvements that enable the Complex Forms and Sprites tab.

improvement.name: Enable Technomancer Tab
improvement.altpage: Enables the character's 'Complex Forms and Sprites' tab, allowing them to purchase Complex Forms and compile Sprites. The character is flagged as a Technomancer for the purposes of quality requirements, but does not receive access to the Submersion tab, unlock their Resonance attribute or receive any of the Resonance skills. Incompatible with improvements that enable the Spells and Spirits tab.

improvement.name: Force Disable Initiation/Submersion Tab
improvement.altpage: Forcibly disables the character's Initiation or Submersion tab, forbidding them from getting metamagics or echoes.

improvement.name: Enable Critter Tab
improvement.altpage: Enables the character's Critter Powers tab, allowing them to buy critter powers. The character is flagged as a Critter.

improvement.name: Cyber-Singularity Seeker/Redliner (Attribute)
improvement.altpage: Grants bonuses to the specified attribute based on the number of cyberlimbs a character has. Special attributes are invalid

improvement.name: Cyber-Singularity Seeker/Redliner (Condition Monitor)
improvement.altpage: Grants bonuses to the character's physical Condition Monitor based on the number of cyberlimbs a character has. See Redliner in Chrome Flesh for more details.

improvement.name: Block Skillgroup Defaulting
improvement.altpage: Prevents the character from seeing dicepool values for skills in the selected skillgroup.

improvement.name: Attribute Level
improvement.altpage: Adds to the selected attribute's base Value, increasing Karma costs for subsequent purchases.

improvement.name: Skill Level
improvement.altpage: Adds to the selected attribute's base Value, increasing Karma costs for subsequent purchases.

improvement.name: KnowSoft
improvement.altpage: Creates a Knowledge Skill that requires the skillsoftaccess improvement to be activated.

improvement.name: Adept Power
improvement.altpage: Creates a free Adept Power. If the selected power already exists, the power will either be marked as free, or have free levels added to it.

improvement.name: Initiative Dice
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the number of Initiative Dice the character receives by the value entered. Positive numbers increase the number of Initiative Dice. Negative numbers reduce the number of Initiative Dice.

improvement.name: Matrix Initiative Passes
improvement.altpage: Adjusts the number of Matrix Initiative Passes the character receives by the value entered. Positive numbers increase the number of Matrix Initiative Passes. Negative numbers reduce the number of Matrix Initiative Passes.

improvement.name: Street Cred Multiplier
improvement.altpage: Increases or reduces the multiplier used to calculate Street Cred.

improvement.name: Bonus Street Cred
improvement.altpage: Increases the character's Street Cred by the listed value.
